ACT V, SCENE 2 (851â€”end). To the three persons at table enter Artemona and the Parasite. They are unseen by the banqueters until they shew themselves (v. 909). Artemona overhears what is pass- ing, surprises Demaenetus aud leads him away from the place of his shame.

The scene is an angry one and written in septenarian trochaics.

Scenes are often made to begin like this in the middle of a con- versation. See Trin. 602, Men. 889, Poen. 959, Ter. Andr. 301, Eun. 391, Haut. 242 &c.
